  "summary": "Malicious code in opentelemetry-plugin-graphql-example (npm)",
  "details": "Package name opentelemetry-plugin-graphql-example combosquats OpenTelemetry. File does.js runs automatically on package installation: it creates a concealed directory, collects host identity data (hostname, OS platform, CPU architecture), and writes that data to a local file. No actual OpenTelemetry functionality, no README, only 3 trivial files — a reconnaissance/staging payload delivered through an npm installation trigger.",
